# V0 USB HID skeleton — xHCI host-controller probe + HID boot-keyboard
# translator. On hardware/QEMU configs without a PS/2 controller
# (T480+, modern Dells, MacBooks via boot-camp), this is the only path
# to a working keyboard. V0 ships controller-detect + root-hub port-
# scan + HID-report-to-ASCII self-test; the transfer-ring engine that
# would actually carry keystrokes off the wire lands in V1. See
# drivers/usb/xhci.ad header comment for the explicit scope boundary.
