    # Plan-9 namespace bind/mount/unmount self-test. Gated on
    # /etc/bind-test (planted by build_initramfs.py when ENABLE_BIND_TEST=1,
    # via scripts/test_bind.sh). Same marker-scan shape as the gates above.
    # bind_selftest() (sys/src/9/port/bind_test.ad) binds a source dir onto
    # a union name and resolves a file THROUGH it (proves the bind redirects
    # the walk), unions a second dir with MBEFORE (proves files from BOTH
    # members are visible + the MBEFORE member shadows a shared name),
    # unmounts (proves the binding reverts), and clones a fresh Pgrp to bind
    # in isolation (proves a child-namespace bind is NOT visible in the
    # parent). Prints its own [bind] lines + a single [bind] PASS. Default
    # boots omit the marker so it never fires unintentionally.
